The idea to use beams of silicon as sensors to measure deflections or changes in resonance frequency is actually quite old. First reports go back to 1968, when Wilfinger et al. [15.2] investigated silicon cantilever structures of 50mm×30mm×8mm\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
